  "texts": [
    "Fog computing thus brings forth low latency (critical for realtime applications), mobility support, heterogeneity, edge location awareness, etc.",
    "The fog layer also assists in augmenting the edge and cloud layers; the fog nodes situated in-between edge nodes and clouds can coordinate with both of them to help provide better user experience.",
    "Mist computingThe Fog and Edge computing paradigms bring computation closer to users and assist in the reuse of edge resources.",
    "A further evolution (and decentralisation) of these concepts has been proposed as Mist Computing [26].",
    "As stated by NIST [27], Mist computing is situated at the extreme edge of the network and can be considered as a light-weight category of Fog Computing."
  ],
